description:
This is Brazil explores and celebrates Brazil's cultural diversity, viewing daily life through the eyes of local chefs, musicians, artists and everyday workers.

Host Fernanda de Paula, a Brazilian-born Australian who is passionate about her homeland, rediscovers the food and people she grew up with and uncovers Brazil's soul.

From the pounding drums of the Afro-Brazilian capital, Salvador, to the floating villages of the Amazon, she meets the people that infuse everyday life in Brazil with passion.
